                            <comment id="15269222" author="hossman" created="Tue, 3 May 2016 18:02:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Distributed cardinality involves serializing a bunch of binary data structures to send them over the wire &amp;#8211; classes like &lt;br/&gt;
HLLSerializationTest already use &lt;tt&gt;@Monster&lt;/tt&gt; on many tests because of the amount of heap required, I suspect the overhead of SSL encryption just pushes &lt;br/&gt;
TestDistributedStatsComponentCardinality over the edge.&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="15269744" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 3 May 2016 22:32:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 2dab1ce40c35a5614237e13c88efbc5820d5ef2f in lucene-solr&apos;s branch refs/heads/branch_6x from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hossman_lucene%40fucit.org&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;hossman_lucene@fucit.org&quot;&gt;hossman_lucene@fucit.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
